<headline>Winter Storm Warning issued February 18 at 3:36AM EST until February 18 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Buffalo</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EST THIS
MORNING...
* WHAT...Heavy snow. Additional snow accumulations of 2 to 3
inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph will produce blowing and
drifting snow.
* WHERE...Niagara and Orleans counties.
* WHEN...Until 9 AM EST this morning.
* IMPACTS...Travel will be very difficult this morning. The
combination of a wintry mix and rapidly falling temperatures
last night will continue to produce icy and hazardous roads this
morning, with snow accumulation on top of ice.</description>
<instruction>Widespread accumulating snow will create dangerous travel
conditions.
Submit snow reports through our website or social media.</instruction>
